</md></sn><sn><md>### Prokaryot vs Eukaryot

![img](https://uen.pressbooks.pub/app/uploads/sites/382/2024/06/U04-001-Comparison-of-prokaryote-and-eukaryote.png)

| Feature                       | Prokaryotes                                | Eukaryotes                                                           |
| ----------------------------- | ------------------------------------------ | -------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Cell type**                 | Simple, primitive                          | Complex, advanced                                                    |
| **Nucleus**                   | Absent (DNA lies in nucleoid)              | Present (DNA enclosed in nuclear membrane)                           |
| **Size**                      | Small (1–10 µm)                            | Large (10–100 µm)                                                    |
| **Cell wall**                 | Present (mainly peptidoglycan in bacteria) | Present in plants and fungi (cellulose or chitin), absent in animals |
| **Membrane-bound organelles** | Absent                                     | Present (e.g., mitochondria, ER, Golgi body)                         |
| **DNA**                       | Circular and naked                         | Linear and associated with histone proteins                          |
| **Ribosomes**                 | 70S type (smaller)                         | 80S type (larger)                                                    |
| **Cell division**             | By binary fission                          | By mitosis or meiosis                                                |
| **Examples**                  | Bacteria, Archaea                          | Plants, Animals, Fungi, Protists                                     |
| **Flagella structure**        | Simple, made of flagellin                  | Complex, made of microtubules (9+2 arrangement)                      |

