:::</md></sn><sn><md>### Introduction

* All the living organism divided in two groups- Plant, Animal
* In 1866 Heckel proposed another group- Protista for lower organism
* After that Group Protista again divided in two group, lower Protista is named as Monera, Protista, Plantae, Animalia
* In 1969 Whittaker proposed a unique classification for all organism and he divided all organism in five group. 

This system is known as Whitakers Five Kingdom concept

